---

{% include "partials/site-header.njk" %}

<header class="musicians-hero">
  {% if site.hero.videoUrl %}
  <video class="musicians-hero__video" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="{{ site.hero.posterUrl }}">
    {% if site.hero.mobileVideoUrl %}
    <source src="{{ site.hero.mobileVideoUrl }}" type="video/mp4" media="(max-width: 720px) and (orientation: portrait)">
    {% endif %}
    <source src="{{ site.hero.videoUrl }}" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
  {% endif %}
  <div class="musicians-hero__vignette" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="musicians-hero__content">
    <p class="musicians-hero__eyebrow">For Musicians</p>
    <h1 class="visually-hidden">For Musicians</h1>
    <div class="musicians-pitch-box">
      <p class="musicians-pitch-box__lead">
        Get your name, album cover, and Spotify in the game.
      </p>
      <p class="musicians-pitch-box__sub">
        All it takes is 4 or 8 bars of your own music, retuned to D# minor at 120 BPM.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="musicians-page">

  <section class="section musicians-intro">
    <h2 class="section__heading musicians-intro__heading">How it works</h2>
    <div class="musicians-intro__grid">
      <div class="musicians-intro__card">
        <span class="musicians-intro__eyebrow">The game</span>
        <p>A pew-pew roguelite where all weapons and gear sync to musical instruments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="musicians-intro__card">
        <span class="musicians-intro__eyebrow">What I need</span>
        <p>A <span class="spec-value">4 or 8 bar</span> slice of your existing music, nudged into <span class="spec-value">D# minor</span> at <span class="spec-value">120 BPM</span>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="musicians-intro__card">
        <span class="musicians-intro__eyebrow">What you get</span>
        <p>Your name, art, and Spotify link on screen every time a player finds your work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-flow">
    <h2 class="section__heading">What players see</h2>
    <ol class="flow-steps">

      <li class="flow-step flow-step--center">
        <div class="flow-step__media-col">
          <div class="flow-step__media">
            <video autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata"
                   aria-hidden="true">
              <source src="/assets/artist-promotion/artist_item_drop.mp4" type="video/mp4">
            </video>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step__body">
          <span class="flow-step__num">01</span>
          <h3>Your weapon drops</h3>
          <p>A player cracks open a loot crate. Out drops a weapon: your name on it, one of your stems loaded into it.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flow-step flow-step--left">
        <div class="flow-step__media-col">
          <div class="flow-step__media">
            <video autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata"
                   aria-hidden="true">
              <source src="/assets/artist-promotion/artist_in_inventory.mp4" type="video/mp4">
            </video>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step__body">
          <span class="flow-step__num">02</span>
          <h3>It rides with them</h3>
          <p>Each weapon is a single instrument from you. Your art sits next to the new loot's stats, and your stem plays seamlessly with whatever the player is already running. Players might mix-and-match stems, or try hunting down the complete set from your track.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="flow-step flow-step--close-up">
        <div class="flow-step__media-col">
          <div class="flow-step__media">
            <video autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata"
                   aria-hidden="true">
              <source src="/assets/artist-promotion/artist_inventory_close_up.mp4" type="video/mp4">
            </video>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step__body">
          <span class="flow-step__num">03</span>
          <h3>One tap to your Spotify</h3>
          <p>The tile links straight to your Spotify, YouTube, or other platform. If a player likes the loop, the rest of your work is one tap away.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-demo-section">
    <h2 class="section__heading">Hear a loop in action</h2>
    <figure class="musicians-demo">
      <div class="musicians-demo__player" data-state="idle">
        <video class="musicians-demo__video" controls playsinline preload="metadata">
          <source src="https://pub-e52e55062eab45daaa777a6bec1f03ca.r2.dev/music_sync_demo.mp4" type="video/mp4">
        </video>
        <button class="musicians-demo__play" type="button" aria-label="Play demo with sound">
          <span class="musicians-demo__play-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <figcaption class="musicians-demo__caption">Hit play with sound on.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <script>
      (function () {
        var wrap = document.currentScript.previousElementSibling.querySelector('.musicians-demo__player');
        if (!wrap) return;
        var video = wrap.querySelector('video');
        var btn = wrap.querySelector('.musicians-demo__play');
        btn.addEventListener('click', function () { video.play(); });
        video.addEventListener('play', function () { wrap.setAttribute('data-state', 'playing'); });
      })();
    </script>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-examples">
    <h2 class="section__heading">Try it in your DAW</h2>
    <p class="musicians-examples__intro">Your bars need to land on spec: <span class="spec-value">120 BPM</span>, <span class="spec-value">D# Minor</span>, <span class="spec-value">4 or 8 bars</span>, looping seamlessly, one isolated instrument per stem.</p>
    <p class="musicians-examples__intro">Drop one of these reference stacks into your DAW and lay your retuned bars over the top, to hear how yours would sit in the mix.</p>
    <div class="musicians-examples__list">
      <a class="musicians-example"
         href="https://pub-e52e55062eab45daaa777a6bec1f03ca.r2.dev/thin_addition_stems.zip"
         download>
        <span class="musicians-example__label">Reference stack 1</span>
        <span class="musicians-example__meta">ZIP · ~25 MB</span>
      </a>
      <a class="musicians-example"
         href="https://pub-e52e55062eab45daaa777a6bec1f03ca.r2.dev/blazed_sneakers_stems.zip"
         download>
        <span class="musicians-example__label">Reference stack 2</span>
        <span class="musicians-example__meta">ZIP · ~25 MB</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <p class="musicians-examples__note">Even one instrument, just 4 bars of your own, is enough to send.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-cta">
    <h2 class="section__heading">Interested?</h2>
    <p>
      Help me promote the game in whatever way feels natural (a tweet, a story, a word to friends in the scene). If we're not already in touch, find me (Tim) in the Discord.
    </p>
    <p>
      Acceptance into the game isn't guaranteed, but credit for any used work is.
    </p>
    <a class="btn--discord" href="{{ site.social.discordInvite }}" rel="noopener">Join the Discord →</a>
  </section>

  <section class="section musicians-tech">
    <h2 class="section__heading musicians-tech__heading">Technical details</h2>
    <ul class="musicians-tech__list">
      <li>A short section of your own music, adjusted so it lands at 120 BPM in D# minor (it almost certainly isn't there already, that's the work).</li>
      <li>Stems, delivered as a ZIP.</li>
      <li>One isolated instrument per stem (each becomes its own weapon, so I can't use a bounced mix).</li>
      <li>44.1 kHz WAV.</li>
      <li>Submit as many stems as you'd like.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</main>
